{"title_page": "Eduardo Machado (footballer)", "text_new": "{{short description|Portuguese footballer}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n | name = Eduardo Machado\n | image =\n | fullname = Eduardo Jos\u00e9 Borges Machado<ref name=Profile>{{cite web|url=https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/edu-machado/boavista/1581-128-18760|title=Edu Machado|publisher=Mais Futebol|language=Portuguese|accessdate=17 April 2020}}</ref>\n | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1990|4|26|df=yes}}<ref name=Profile/>         \n | birth_place = [[Chaves, Portugal]]<ref name=Profile/>\n | height = {{height|m=1.75}}<ref name=Profile/>\n | position = [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|Right back]], [[Midfielder]]\n | currentclub = [[Leix\u00f5es S.C.|Leix\u00f5es]]<br/>(on loan from [[Boavista F.C.|Boavista]])\n | clubnumber = 20\n | youthyears1 = 1998\u20132009 | youthclubs1 = [[G.D. Chaves|Chaves]]\n | years1 = 2009\u20132013 | clubs1 = [[G.D. Chaves|Chaves]] | caps1 = 77 | goals1 = 2 \n | years2 = 2013\u20132014 | clubs2 = [[S.C. Freamunde|Freamunde]] | caps2 = 33 | goals2 = 3\n | years3 = 2014\u20132016 | clubs3 = [[C.D. Tondela|Tondela]] | caps3 = 52 | goals3 = 1\n | years4 = 2016 | clubs4 = [[G.D. Chaves|Chaves]] | caps4 = 8 | goals4 = 0\n | years5 = 2016\u2013 | clubs5 = [[Boavista F.C.|Boavista]] | caps5 = 49 | goals5 = 0\n | years6 = 2020\u2013 | clubs6 = \u2192 [[Leix\u00f5es S.C.|Leix\u00f5es]] (loan) | caps6 = 3 | goals6 = 0\n | totalcaps = | totalgoals = \n | nationalyears1 = 2011 | nationalteam1 = [[Portugal national under-21 football team|Portugal U21]] | nationalcaps1 = 5 | nationalgoals1 = 0 \n | club-update = 26 January 2020\n | nationalteam-update =\n}}\n\n'''Eduardo Jos\u00e9 Borges Machado''' (born 26 April 1990) is a [[Portugal|Portuguese]] professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Leix\u00f5es S.C.]] on loan from [[Boavista F.C.]] as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|right back]] or a [[Midfielder#Wide midfielder|right midfielder]].\n\n==Club career==\nBorn in [[Chaves, Portugal|Chaves]], Machado played youth football with local club [[G.D. Chaves]]. He appeared in five [[LigaPro|Segunda Liga]] matches in [[2009\u201310 Liga de Honra|2009\u201310]] (relegation), then spent the following three seasons with the team in the [[Portuguese Second Division|third division]]; on 13 April 2010, he scored twice to help defeat hosts [[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Naval 1\u00ba de Maio]] 2\u20131 in the second leg of [[2009\u201310 Ta\u00e7a de Portugal|the semi-finals]] of the [[Ta\u00e7a de Portugal]],<ref name=Returns>{{cite news|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/detalhe/edu-machado-volta-a-casa?act=0&est=Aberto|title=Edu Machado volta a casa|trans-title=Edu Machado returns home|newspaper=[[Record (newspaper)|Record]]|language=Portuguese|date=15 January 2016|accessdate=17 April 2020}}</ref> and also appeared in [[2010 Ta\u00e7a de Portugal Final|the decisive game]] against [[FC Porto]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.dn.pt/desporto/fc-porto/a-final-de-2010-ja-e-uma-memoria-distante-para-estes-chaves-e-fc-porto-5504121.html|title=A final de 2010 j\u00e1 \u00e9 uma mem\u00f3ria distante para estes Chaves e FC Porto|trans-title=The 2010 final is already a distant memory for these Chaves and FC Porto|newspaper=[[Di\u00e1rio de Not\u00edcias]]|first=Rui|last=Marques Sim\u00f5es|language=Portuguese|date=17 November 2016|accessdate=17 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nAfter spending the [[2013\u201314 Campeonato Nacional de Seniores|2013\u201314 campaign]] also in the third tier with [[S.C. Freamunde]], helping his side promote as champions, Machado signed with [[C.D. Tondela]] in the summer of 2014. He contributed with 41 games and one goal<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.futebol365.pt/artigo/124102-segunda-liga-tondela-vence-benfica-b-e-ultrapassa-os-encarnados/|title=Segunda Liga: Tondela vence Benfica B e ultrapassa os encarnados|trans-title=Second League: Tondela defeat Benfica B and overtake reds|publisher=Futebol 365|first=Manuel|last=Resendes|language=Portuguese|date=29 November 2014|accessdate=17 April 2020}}</ref> in [[2014\u201315 Segunda Liga|his first year]], in a first-ever promotion to the [[Primeira Liga]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/1a-liga/tondela/noticias/quim-machado-de-saida-do-tondela-4592335.html|title=Quim Machado de sa\u00edda do Tondela|trans-title=Quim Machado leaving Tondela|newspaper=[[O Jogo]]|first=Concei\u00e7\u00e3o|last=Diogo|language=Portuguese|date=27 May 2015|accessdate=17 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nMachado made his debut in the [[Portuguese football league system|Portuguese top flight]] on 14 August 2015, playing 90 minutes in a 1\u20132 home loss against [[Sporting CP]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.dn.pt/desporto/sporting/interior/penalti-no-final-salvou-sporting-frente-ao-estreante-tondela-4729343.html|title=Pen\u00e1lti no final salvou Sporting frente ao estreante Tondela|trans-title=Late penalty saved Sporting against newcomers Tondela|newspaper=Di\u00e1rio de Not\u00edcias|first=Jo\u00e3o|last=Ruela|language=Portuguese|date=14 August 2015|accessdate=17 April 2020}}</ref> The following [[transfer window]], he was released and returned to Chaves.<ref name=Returns/>\n\nOn 26 May 2016, Machado joined [[Boavista F.C.|Boavista FC]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/mercado/liga/oficial-edu-machado-ex-chaves-e-reforco-do-boavista|title=OFICIAL: Edu Machado (ex-Chaves) \u00e9 refor\u00e7o do Boavista|trans-title=OFFICIAL: Edu Machado (ex-Chaves) is a Boavista addition|publisher=Mais Futebol|language=Portuguese|date=26 May 2016|accessdate=17 April 2020}}</ref> He missed the vast majority of [[2017\u201318 Primeira Liga|2017\u201318]], due to an [[anterior cruciate ligament]] rupture to his right knee.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.jn.pt/desporto/edu-machado-fora-dos-relvados-durante-sete-meses-8802911.html|title=Edu Machado fora dos relvados durante sete meses|trans-title=Edu Machado out of the pitches for seven months|newspaper=[[Jornal de Not\u00edcias]]|language=Portuguese|date=27 September 2017|accessdate=17 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 8 January 2020, Machado was loaned to [[Leix\u00f5es S.C.]] of the second level until 30 June.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/2a-liga/noticias/oficial-leixoes-reforca-se-no-boavista-11682544.html|title=Oficial: Leix\u00f5es refor\u00e7a o plantel com lateral vindo do Boavista|trans-title=Official: Leix\u00f5es bolster squad with fullback from Boavista|newspaper=O Jogo|language=Portuguese|date=8 January 2020|accessdate=16 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nMachado won five [[Cap (sport)|caps]] for the [[Portugal national under-21 football team|Portuguese under-21 side]], all in 2011. His first came on 9 February, when he played the second half of the 3\u20131 [[Exhibition game|friendly]] victory over [[Sweden national under-21 football team|Sweden]] in [[Cartaxo]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.record.xl.pt/futebol/selecoes/detalhe/sub-21-portugal-bate-suecia-no-cartaxo-683329.html|title=Sub-21: Portugal bate Su\u00e9cia no Cartaxo|trans-title=Under-21: Portugal beat Sweden in Cartaxo|newspaper=Record|language=Portuguese|date=9 February 2011|accessdate=17 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{ForaDeJogo|199004260002}}\n*[https://www.fpf.pt/Jogadores/Jogador/playerId/616500 National team data] {{in lang|pt}}\n*{{Soccerway|eduardo-jose-borges-machado/126466}}\n\n{{Leix\u00f5es S.C. squad}}\n<!-- {{Boavista F.C. squad}} -->\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Machado, Eduardo}}\n[[Category:1990 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Chaves, Portugal]]\n[[Category:Portuguese footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Primeira Liga players]]\n[[Category:LigaPro players]]\n[[Category:Portuguese Second Division players]]\n[[Category:G.D. Chaves players]]\n[[Category:S.C. Freamunde players]]\n[[Category:C