ssociation football)#Full-back|right back]] or a [[Midfielder#Wide midfielder|right midfielder]].\n\n==Club career==\nBorn in [[Chaves, Portugal|Chaves]], Machado played youth football with local club [[G.D. Chaves]]. He appeared in five [[LigaPro|Segunda Liga]] matches in [[2009\u201310 Liga de Honra|2009\u201310]] (relegation), then spent the following three seasons with the team in the [[Portuguese Second Division|third division]]; on 13 April 2010, he scored twice to help defeat hosts [[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Naval 1\u00ba de Maio]] 2\u20131 in the second leg of [[2009\u201310 Ta\u00e7a de Portugal|the semi-finals]] of the [[Ta\u00e7a de Portugal]],<ref name=Returns>{{cite news|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/detalhe/edu-machado-volta-a-casa?act=0&est=Aberto|title=Edu Machado volta a casa|trans-title=Edu Machado returns home|newspaper=[[Record (newspaper)|Record]]|language=Portuguese|date=15 January 2016|accessdate=17 April 2020}}</ref> and also appeared in [[2010 Ta\u00e7a de Portugal Final|the decisive game]] against [[FC Porto]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.dn.pt/desporto/fc-porto/a-final-de-2010-ja-e-uma-memoria-distante-para-estes-chaves-e-fc-porto-5504121.html|title=A final de 2010 j\u00e1 \u00e9 uma mem\u00f3ria distante para estes Chaves e FC Porto|trans-title=The 2010 final is already a distant memory for these Chaves and FC Porto|newspaper=[[Di\u00e1rio de Not\u00edcias]]|first=Rui|last=Marques Sim\u00f5es|language=Portuguese|date=17 November 2016|accessdate=17 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nAfter spending the [[2013\u201314 Campeonato Nacional de Seniores|2013\u201314 campaign]] also in the third tier with [[S.C. Freamunde]], helping his side promote as champions, Machado signed with [[C.D. Tondela]] in the summer of 2014. He contributed with 41 games and one goal<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.futebol365.pt/artigo/124102-segunda-liga-tondela-vence-benfica-b-e-ultrapassa-os-encarnados/|title=Segunda Liga: Tondela vence Benfica B e ultrapas